('04d40908-5045-4f59-9721-c3ee18cc549f', 'admin', '2019-06-09 14:31', 1, '\r\n== Step 1 == \r\n{{/TeLKtV3J-FwoBg7trvAzwvoN1DB5_Q2pxA.png|}}\r\n === Open the Settings menu in Google Chrome === \r\n----\r\n== Step 2 == \r\n{{/eExbo1cWjNJwe-JzPWyLmV2ebXnd7r-4uQ.png|}}\r\n === Click on  === <em> === Show Advanced Settings. === </em>\r\n----\r\n== Step 3 == \r\n{{/tWGoRL7trJqW1oWXtk62apKGKg3DUdveYw.png|}}\r\nSelect Clear Browsing Data under the Privacy section.\r\n----\r\n== Step 4 == \r\n== {{/dQhT7zBRk7fuAcWpaJXXC9Wz69GaK_6KaA.png|}} ==  === Select the following: === \r\n<ul>\n<li>\r\n === Cookies and other site and plugins === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Cached images and files === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Obliterate the following items from: the beginning of time. === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click Clear Browsing Data === </li>\n</ul>\r\n----\r\n== Step 5 == \r\n === Restart your browser. === \r\n', @liid);
