('af4aeb4c-66dc-46f5-a274-4724876572e2', 'admin', '2019-06-09 14:31', 1, '\r\n== Step 1: == \r\n== {{/NOvwb0L_HPvtEiRD2dDIdNq2XVEkW0FbEA.png|}} == \r\n==  == \r\n === Enter the <em>Invoices </em>menu under <em>Accounts Receivable.</em> === \r\n ===  === \r\n----\r\n== Step 2: == \r\n{{/Ym_VWGIF3XUwtP7b5knbiVF3fFHFm08Y0g.png|}} ===  ===  === \r\n === \r\n === Select the batch of invoice and select  === <em> === Details. === </em>\r\n<em> ===  === </em>\r\n----\r\n== Step 3: == \r\n== {{/l57p9FMCBQWVvMNZKDZVskvTjD59uPbM0w.png|}} == \r\n === Select the invoice that you want to allocate a receipt to, and click  === <em> === Allocate. === </em>\r\n<em> ===  === </em>\r\n----\r\n== Step 4: == \r\n{{/YPUUaVo2ctIfQMtozqD49_6jJJmXkuTZPg.png|}}\r\n==  == \r\n === Select the corresponding Receipt from the <em>Outstanding Transactions</em> and click the upwards pointing arrow. === \r\n==  == \r\n ===  === \r\n----\r\n== Step 5: == \r\n{{/zho5ZMuqjpCn3pNOXQZ59AoNo-PRh8PgpQ.png|}}\r\n === Click <em>Save </em>to save changes. === \r\n ===  === \r\n ===  === \r\n----\r\n==  ==  ===  === \r\n==  ==  ===  === \r\n ===  === \r\n==  == \r\n', @liid);
