('b85d7d80-1d03-4ec6-9e89-b408249ed0f8', 'admin', '2019-06-09 14:31', 1, '\r\n== Example == \r\n === The debtor has paid the full amount ($4800) of a levy before due date, accidentally ignoring the discount amount.  === \r\n === You want to ensure that the debtor still receives the discount and the remainder of the paid amount is stored as credit.  === \r\n ===  === \r\n----\r\n ===  === \r\n== Step 1 == \r\n{{/zcv5p-TIhv2f0x_Izzo2trwyE-U1ctho9g.png|}}\r\n === \r\n === \r\n === Enter the <em>Receipts </em>menu under Accounts Receivable.  === \r\n----\r\n== Step 2 == \r\n{{/jg4jBgMfnCKa3p9UzN5haM-jEITfZTTnSQ.png|}}\r\n === \r\n === \r\n === Select the appropriate receipt and click "Allocate" === \r\n----\r\n== Step 3 == \r\n{{/8nU-02S2uV9SWNuzBEiDrWB2R_cmDt0TAQ.png|}}\r\n === Select the corresponding Invoice from the Outstanding Transactions and click the upwards pointing arrow. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 4 == \r\n{{/u5I2RhEW4e65opyE4zyX0L6eO9H3h3-wpQ.png|}}\r\n<ul>\n<li>\r\n === Select the invoice and click edit.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click the 10% Discount to automatically fill the discount amount.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Adjust the Paid amount so that the Paid + Discount amount equals the Gross Amount. === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click the Save icon.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click the Save button to confirm changes.  === </li>\n</ul> === Note: The non-allocated amount will be stored in the debtors account as a credit. === \r\n----\r\n', @liid);
