('a503098c-27f5-47b5-9d53-85d8bfe89055', 'admin', '2019-06-09 14:31', 1, '\r\n== \r\n == \r\n== Step 1 == \r\n{{/1SIIQPQecwWLPSqDTHRLErljp9w97Q6T1g.png|}}\r\n === Go to the Invoices menu under the Accounts Payable tab. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 2 == \r\n{{/Qro8Zu23CoRP_cK5RWkGJMyW4nte9aQL6Q.png|}}\r\n === \r\n === \r\n === Click <em>Add</em> to create a new Creditor Invoice === \r\n----\r\n== Step 3 == \r\n === \r\n === \r\n === {{/zz4XsnB3zBih3huZJx1TMI1mFvyufgZx_A.png|}} === \r\n === \r\n === \r\n === Create Creditor Invoice and select the unit you wish to On Charge part of the invoice to. === \r\n === A debtor invoice to the unit will be created automatically. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 4 == \r\n{{/cXNi41BTqBSBLDVHudC6rLmeFCl_Pcdv3g.png|}}\r\n === Go into the<em> Accounts Receivable - Invoice </em>menu, select the automatically generated invoice and click <em>Details</em>. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 5 == \r\n{{/5IKDTMXarZbFHXpzzfjnUUlV4SB3SeeYIQ.png|}}\r\n === Here you will see the on charged invoice. Click <em>details </em>to view more information about this invoice. === \r\n----\r\n ===  === \r\n', @liid);
