('830aa30e-df44-4563-b201-4a05cd545788', 'admin', '2019-06-09 14:31', 1, '\r\n== Step 1 == \r\n== : == \r\n{{/8q3xp4SCYu2vL_uhheubvqrzBgEFpb143Q.png|}}\r\n === Enter the <em>CCredit Notes</em> Menu under Accounts Payable. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 2: == \r\n{{/gYOADapr-gmDq4URL3VRwdqrd2B-iTafcw.png|}}\r\n === Click <em>Add </em>to create a new Credit Note. === \r\n----\r\n== Step 3: == \r\n{{/glkIxhJ7u_Pt2kFrxgebC-pTawLo3uef8A.png|}}\r\n === \r\n === \r\n<ol>\n<li>\r\n === Credit Note <em>Number</em> will be automatically generated, you can manually override this if necessary. === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Select the <em>Creditor </em>who issued the credit note.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Enter the <em>Date </em>the Credit Note was issued.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click the <em>+</em> icon in the bottom menu. === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Select the corresponding <em>Chart Code</em>. === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Enter the <em>Gross </em>amount of the credit note.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Tick the <em>GST </em>tickbox if it is GST inclusive.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click the <em>save </em>icon in the bottom menu.  === </li>\n<li>\r\n === Click S<em>ave </em>on the left hand menu to confirm the Credit Note.  === </li>\n</ol>\r\n----\r\n', @liid);
